-- India top court dismisses Nokia appeal over asset transfer to Microsoft 
-- By Suchitra Mohanty
-- Fri Mar 14, 2014 06:42AM EDT
-- None



NEW DELHI, March 14 (Reuters) - India's Supreme Court on Friday dismissed Nokia's appeal challenging a lower court order over transferring ownership of its local mobile phone plant, which is the subject of a tax dispute, to Microsoft Corp <MSFT.O>.

The Supreme Court upheld a verdict by the Delhi High Court and ordered Nokia to give a guarantee for 35 billion rupees ($572.5 million).